text:
¬†@bakamitaii1572¬† I mute them all, too. Well, except one. I mainly concerned with just the action being synced up. 

Just start all of them at the times that I listed and keep them muted and you will have 5 simultaneous perspectives.
author: @R3_dacted0

text: ¬†@R3_dacted0¬† thanks I can‚Äôt help but feel they unsync themselves though somehow I‚Äôll see them talk while their avatar isn‚Äôt and I‚Äôll reset back into a time consuming resync I think it‚Äôs quite amazing how you guys can do it without a fault by the way how do you play each video at the same time
author: @bakamitaii1572

text:
¬†@bakamitaii1572¬† Most of us don't get it perfect. I normally focus on one perspective and glance at others when they do something interesting, so it doesn't bother me if it's off by a couple seconds.

I play each VOD until I hear them say a specific line near the beginning and pause it there. Once all of them are lined up and muted, I unpause them one at a time quickly. If I notice one video is ahead of the others, I pause it for a second to let the others catch up. When they sleep or use in-game chat it's easy to see when one video is ahead of the others. By the time they were searching for the portal, I had it synced. If you need to take a break, just pause and unpause in the same order.
